902449294924736, 0.08332813531160355, -0.007890559732913971, -0.07738997042179108, 0.036945559084415436, 0.03750878572463989, 0.004423544276505709, 0.024127349257469177, 0.04598238319158554, 0.058917611837387085, -0.06642661243677139, -0.013583495281636715], "turn_range": [0, 6]}, {"id": "acd5a3d2-3516-4b63-8dd0-9dd53d838802", "chunk_index": 1, "text": "USER: Tevi doesn't know a Skylar\nASSISTANT:  There it is. Tevi doesn't know them, so it's a scam or a wrong-number hustle. \n\nCommon next moves from these types:\n- They'll try to pay upfront with a fake check/Zelle\u53cd\u8f6c and ask you to \"refund the overage\"\n- Or it's a setup to get you to a vacant property to case tools/gear\n- Or just a phishing farm harvesting active numbers\n\nJust ignore or block. Don't even reply \"wrong number\"\u2014that confirms the line is active and monitored by a human. \n\nIf you already responded, no big deal, but cut it off now. If they sent any links or follow-up texts about payment, delete. \n\nAnything else weird in the message, or was it literally just that one text?", "embedding": [-0.1223461925983429, 0.07903915643692017, -0.002938619116321206, -0.02280367538332939, -0.06081615015864372, -0.06770490854978561, 0.09608066827058792, -0.04357590526342392, 0.034080870449543, -0.020743250846862793, 0.05817217752337456, 0.03203631564974785, 0.02190305106341839, -0.08635536581277847, -0.0804436206817627, -0.03306221589446068, -0.004085407126694918, -0.1065756231546402, -0.03135271742939949, -0.0031935060396790504, -0.028186742216348648, 0.07887100428342819, 0.020162180066108704, 0.03220289573073387, 0.019092602655291557, -0.035844605416059494, -0.037433966994285583, 0.045842405408620834, -0.04378872364759445, 0.04464099928736687, 0.04730762168765068, 0.12625889480113983, -0.008012025617063046, 0.0053495001047849655, 0.012851470150053501, 0.029169343411922455, 0.007780017331242561, -0.030676983296871185, -0.07190714031457901, -0.04214046895503998, 0.03449828922748566, -0.1024180